  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">From trash to cash: turning plastic pollution into economic opportunity</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The long-term objective of the project is to contribute to the achievement of SDG 14.1, to reduce the amount of plastic waste from land-based activities entering the ocean whilst at the same time, improving livelihoods. This will be done through increasing plastic collection and recycling in Yola city in Adamawa state, Nigeria, and by strengthening partnerships between the private sector and the informal waste sector (IWS) globally.</narrative>
  </description>
